    <string name="service_off_help">Why it keeps turning off</string>
    <string name="service_help_title">Keeping the service running</string>
    <string name="got_it">Got it</string>
    <string name="service_help_body">On some Android devices (especially those with aggressive battery management, such as Xiaomi, Huawei, etc.), the system may turn off Appause\'s accessibility service after you clear background apps or restart the phone. This is the system\'s background management, not an Appause bug.\n\nTo keep it running:\n• Allow Appause to autostart in your phone\'s app settings.\n• Set battery optimization to no restrictions.\n• Lock Appause in the recent-tasks screen.\n\nThen re-enable the service in Accessibility settings.</string>

